rvbf - RISC-V Brainfuck Interpreter
===================================

A minimal Brainfuck interpreter written in RISC-V32 assembly, targeting Linux.

Who am I kidding... Its a toy ...

You gots to have riscv toolchain from gnu or someplace else to build the thing.
`riscv64-unknown-linux-gnu-gcc` should do the trick.
Oh and an emulator would be nice to have too... `qemu` should work well.

If you are a nix user... well... you know what to do.

Now that everything is setup just run:

`riscv64-unknown-linux-gnu-gcc -nostdlib -static -mabi=ilp32 -march=rv32i interp.s -o rvbf`

followed by:

`qemu-riscv32 ./rvbf path/to/program.bf`

A simple test program is already given.

